\p
\v 10-12 King Solomon gave to the queen of Sheba everything that she wanted. He gave her more than she had given to him. Then she and those who came with her returned to her own land.  
\p \add In the ships that belonged to King Hiram,\add* Hiram’s workers and Solomon’s workers brought gold from Ophir. They also brought \w a|strong="H3068"\w* large amount of juniper wood and gems. King Solomon \add told his workers\add* to use that wood to make railings in the temple and in his palace and also to make harps and lyres for the musicians. That wood was the the finest wood that had ever been seen in Israel.   
\s1 Solomon’s wealth  
\p
