\p
\v 1 \w When|strong="H6213"\w* Abijah died, \w he|strong="H6213"\w* \w was|strong="H3068"\w* \w buried|strong="H6213"\w* \w in|strong="H3068"\w* \add the part of Jerusalem called\add* ‘\w The|strong="H6213"\w* City \w of|strong="H3068"\w* David’. \w His|strong="H3068"\w* son Asa became \w the|strong="H6213"\w* king. \w While|strong="H5869"\w* Asa \w was|strong="H3068"\w* ruling, \w there|strong="H3477"\w* \w was|strong="H3068"\w* \w peace|strong="H3477"\w* \w in|strong="H3068"\w* Judah \w for|strong="H6213"\w* ten years.   
\s1 King Asa’s rule in Judah  
\p
\v 2 Asa did things \w that|strong="H4196"\w* \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* \w his|strong="H5493"\w* God considers \w to|strong="H4196"\w* \w be|strong="H7665"\w* right \w and|strong="H4196"\w* good.  
\v 3 \w His|strong="H3068"\w* \w workers|strong="H6213"\w* got rid \w of|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H6213"\w* altars \w to|strong="H3068"\w* worship foreign gods \w that|strong="H3068"\w* \w were|strong="H3063"\w* \w on|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H6213"\w* \w high|strong="H6213"\w* hills. \w They|strong="H3068"\w* smashed \w the|strong="H6213"\w* sacred stone pillars \w and|strong="H3063"\w* cut down \w the|strong="H6213"\w* poles \w for|strong="H6213"\w* worshiping \add the goddess\add* Asherah.  
\v 4 Asa commanded \w the|strong="H3605"\w* people \w of|strong="H5892"\w* \w Judah|strong="H3063"\w* \w to|strong="H6440"\w* worship \add only\add* \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w*, \w the|strong="H3605"\w* God \w whom|strong="H6440"\w* \w their|strong="H3605"\w* ancestors worshiped, \w and|strong="H3063"\w* \w to|strong="H6440"\w* obey \w his|strong="H3605"\w* laws \w and|strong="H3063"\w* commands.  
\v 5 \w His|strong="H3068"\w* \w workers|strong="H1129"\w* destroyed \w all|strong="H5973"\w* \w the|strong="H3588"\w* shrines \w on|strong="H5117"\w* \w the|strong="H3588"\w* hilltops \w and|strong="H3063"\w* \w the|strong="H3588"\w* altars \w for|strong="H3588"\w* burning incense \add to idols\add* \w in|strong="H8141"\w* \w every|strong="H8141"\w* \w town|strong="H5892"\w* \w in|strong="H8141"\w* \w Judah|strong="H3063"\w*. \w As|strong="H3068"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* result, \w there|strong="H3068"\w* \w was|strong="H3068"\w* \w peace|strong="H8252"\w* \w while|strong="H3588"\w* Asa ruled \w the|strong="H3588"\w* kingdom \add of Judah\add*.  
\v 6 \w His|strong="H3068"\w* \w workers|strong="H1129"\w* \w built|strong="H1129"\w* \w cities|strong="H5892"\w* \w and|strong="H3063"\w* \w constructed|strong="H1129"\w* \w walls|strong="H2346"\w* \w around|strong="H5439"\w* \w them|strong="H6440"\w*. \w No|strong="H6440"\w* army attacked \w Judah|strong="H3063"\w* during \w that|strong="H3588"\w* \w time|strong="H6440"\w*, \w because|strong="H3588"\w* \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* enabled \w them|strong="H6440"\w* \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w have|strong="H3068"\w* \w peace|strong="H5117"\w*.   
\p
\v 7 Asa said \w to|strong="H1961"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* people \w of|strong="H1368"\w* \w Judah|strong="H3063"\w*, “\w We|strong="H3605"\w* should protect \w these|strong="H3605"\w* towns \w by|strong="H1961"\w* building walls around \w them|strong="H5375"\w*, \w with|strong="H1869"\w* watchtowers \w and|strong="H3967"\w* gates \w that|strong="H3605"\w* \w have|strong="H1961"\w* bars. \w This|strong="H5375"\w* country still \w belongs|strong="H1961"\w* \w to|strong="H1961"\w* \w us|strong="H1961"\w* \w because|strong="H3605"\w* \w we|strong="H3068"\w* \w have|strong="H1961"\w* requested \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* \w our|strong="H3605"\w* God \w to|strong="H1961"\w* \w help|strong="H1961"\w* \w us|strong="H1961"\w*. \w We|strong="H3605"\w* requested \w him|strong="H3605"\w* \w for|strong="H3605"\w* \w his|strong="H3605"\w* \w help|strong="H1961"\w*, \w and|strong="H3967"\w* \w he|strong="H3605"\w* \w has|strong="H1961"\w* \w given|strong="H5375"\w* \w us|strong="H1961"\w* peace \w in|strong="H3063"\w* \w our|strong="H3605"\w* \w entire|strong="H3605"\w* country.” \w So|strong="H1961"\w* \w they|strong="H3605"\w* built buildings \w and|strong="H3967"\w* prospered.   
\p
